<br>
What's sure is that people did it, and it took only 20 years to build the Great Pyramid at Cheops.  So they certainly had efficient methods.  The people worked on the off season, when not planting fields.  No slaves were involved.  It was a communal effort, a societal goal urging them on, and they could all take part and be proud.  <br>
